Last week 12 fintech from USA and EU raised more than $1.1 Billion. Some pretty cool ideas. Here is the list with amounts and one-liners.
2022-09-20 23:15:23
"**Europe**  
[Cledara](https://www.linkedin.com/company/cledara/) $20M, software for managing subscriptions  
[CANDIS](https://www.linkedin.com/company/candis-gmbh/) $16M, accounts payable software  
[Claimer ](https://www.linkedin.com/company/claimer/)$4.2M, claims for R&D credits  
[Wayflyer](https://www.linkedin.com/company/wayflyer/) $200M, revenue-based financing  
[Portofino Technologies](https://www.linkedin.com/company/portofino-technologies/) $50M, crypto trading platform  
[Ownera](https://www.linkedin.com/company/ownera/) $20M, the trading network for tokenized assets  


**USA**  
[SavvyFi](https://www.linkedin.com/company/savvyfi/) $4.9M, helps pay off student debt  
powerfintech $316M, credit card issuing infrastructure  
[Ratio](https://www.linkedin.com/company/ratio-tech/) $411M, revenue-based financing  
[Denim](https://www.linkedin.com/company/join-denim/) $126M, a working capital provider for the freight industry  
[Payall Payment Systems, Inc.](https://www.linkedin.com/company/payall-payment-systems/) $10M, a cross-border processor for banks  
[Allocations](https://www.linkedin.com/company/allocations/) $5M, alternative investing 

